ors can be defined using individual \\[mon.x\\] entries for each monitor or a single \\[mon\\] entry for all monitors. I found the former to be more common for clients (such as SC and NC in euca's case) interacting with Ceph cluster.\r\n\r\n{{mon_initial_members}} applies to the Ceph storage cluster (rather than the client), it is used by the cluster to establish quorum. When there are multiple monitors, specifying a subset of these monitors as the initial members reduces the time it takes for the cluster to come online. More about this here - http://ceph.com/docs/master/rados/configuration/mon-config-ref/#initial-members. I don't think it has any meaning to Ceph clients and can be removed from the ceph.conf file without any adverse effects\r\n\r\n{{mon_host}} is also related to initial members and for use in \\[global\\] scope only as per the Ceph documentation http://ceph.com/docs/master/rados/configuration/ceph-conf/#common-settings. \r\n\r\nIt looks like the initial ceph.conf that was uploaded to the wiki was the same as the one that was used to configure the Ceph cluster. Some of the configuration used for configuring server side of things need not be exposed to the clients. With that said, I did not remove anything from that ceph.conf file. I only added the monitor entries. I think it would be safe and correct to remove {{mon_host}} and {{mon_initial_members}} from the ceph.conf files used by SCs and NCs\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=swathi","name":"swathi","key":"swathi","accountId":"557058:ab7e71b5-781c-49ea-9f4d-ea9148c88f03","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/d6487612d6674329ecef11be0a95552b?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dswathi%26avatarId%3D17901%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/d6487612d6674329ecef11be0a95552b?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerI